WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.720
Let me show you something real quick about communicating science.

00:00:02.720 --> 00:00:07.920
If you code or analyze data and need to communicate results based on your work, Cordo should definitely

00:00:07.920 --> 00:00:09.160
be your friend.

00:00:09.160 --> 00:00:12.120
Cordo helps you publish your technical work beautifully anywhere.

00:00:12.120 --> 00:00:16.559
By published technical work, whether you're an analyst, scientist, data scientist, or

00:00:16.559 --> 00:00:20.959
developer, we're often doing exploratory analysis and development work in some IDE or notebook

00:00:20.959 --> 00:00:22.280
or text editor.

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:26.160
When you have results to share, that work is the result of code, sometimes stored in

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:28.120
multiple files and notebooks.

00:00:28.120 --> 00:00:32.880
With Cordo, you start with your code as the core of your work, wherever or however you

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:34.119
prefer to do that.

00:00:34.119 --> 00:00:37.660
And then by beautifully, we mean, it's one thing to build up these insights inside a

00:00:37.660 --> 00:00:42.000
notebook or across multiple projects, and it's another thing to craft that all into

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:45.560
a succinct, singular narrative ready to share with others.

00:00:45.560 --> 00:00:49.459
You may want to combine narrative, code, the output of that code.

00:00:49.459 --> 00:00:53.099
That could be as simple as a set of slides or text for printer for the web.

00:00:53.099 --> 00:00:55.880
Or you may want to offer your audience something interactive so they could dig deeper into

00:00:55.880 --> 00:00:56.880
the data.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:58.919
Cordo helps your audience understand these insights best.

